<subSubSection id="C368652E935F8E02F2AAFF4DFBE0FED6" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935F8E02F2AAFF4DFBE0FED6" blockId="6.[151,1437,223,646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935F8E02F2AAFF4DFBFCFED6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147313" collectorName="J. Serrano" location="St. Ilyrion" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935F8E02F024FF4DFD51FF32" box="[537,640,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F1E4FF4DFBE3FF32" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[985,1074,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F1E4FF4DFBE3FF32" box="[985,1074,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">pumilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Gallia mer.”, “ 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F71AFF4DFAA4FF32" box="[1319,1397,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">tibialis</emphasis>
<location id="8EAD607E935F8E02F743FF4DFF39FED6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DB87B3935F8E02F2AAFF05FD5CFD4E:8EAD607E935F8E02F743FF4DFF39FED6" name="St. Ilyrion" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">St. Ilyrion</location>
?” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935F8E02F301FE91FE7EFED6" box="[316,431,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F3E9FE91FCEBFED6" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[468,826,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F3E9FE91FD4FFED6" box="[468,670,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">Harpalus pumilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F098FE91FCEBFED6" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[677,826,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935F8E02F190FE96FBF2FED6" box="[941,1059,259,286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935F8E02F2FAFEB5FD5CFD4E" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935F8E02F2FAFEB5FD5CFD4E" blockId="6.[151,1437,223,646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">
The individual I hereby design as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935F8E02F079FEB5FD7AFE8A" box="[580,683,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">lectotype</typeStatus>
has labels with the original writing of Dejean stating “Gallia mer”. I saw a second specimen with a card attached to the pin stating “TYPE”, but without any original label hand-written by Dejean, and there was no statement of authorship of designation. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F1F7FEE2FB35FE42" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[970,1252,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F1F7FEE2FB97FE42" box="[970,1094,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. pumilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F673FEFDFB35FE42" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[1102,1252,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(not 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F71DFEE2FEF5FE66" authority="Sturm, 1818" authorityName="Sturm" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F71DFEE2FA4CFE42" box="[1312,1437,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. pumilus</emphasis>
Sturm, 1818
</taxonomicName>
) is currently considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F0D9FE06FB9AFE66" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[740,1099,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcylindricus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F0D9FE06FC7AFE66" box="[740,939,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. subcylindricus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F189FE01FB9AFE66" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[948,1099,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F666FE01FB24FE66" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[1115,1269,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="188 - 278" refId="ref11264" refString="Kataev, B. M. (1989) New data on the ground-beetles of the genera Pangus and Harpalus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) with a revision of some Palaeartic species groups Nasekomye Mongolii. Vol. 10. Nauka, Leningrad, 188 - 278. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Kataev, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F73EFE01FF02FE1A" author="Marggi, W. &amp; Luka, H. &amp; Huber, C. &amp; Wrase, D. W. &amp; Durrer, H." pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="195 - 202" refId="ref11838" refString="Marggi, W., Luka, H., Huber, C., Wrase, D. W. &amp; Durrer, H. (2010) Harpalus (s. str.) subcylindricus Dejean, 1829 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) auch in der Schweiz und im Elsass (F). Entomologische Blatter, 106, 195 - 202." type="journal article" year="2010">Marggi et al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F2E0FE2AFE34FE1A" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[221,485,439,466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="1810" refId="ref11718" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 c) Subtribe Harpalina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 515 - 562." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase 2017c</bibRefCitation>
). Although Dejean described first 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F15CFE2AFC0DFE1A" authorityName="Sturm" authorityYear="1818" box="[865,988,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F15CFE2AFC0DFE1A" box="[865,988,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. pumilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this name entered in homonym with 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F7BCFE2AFE56FE3E" authority="Sturm, 1818" authorityName="Sturm" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F7BCFE2AFF21FE3E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. pumilus</emphasis>
Sturm, 1818
</taxonomicName>
. As I did not dissect the aedeagus of the type of I couldn’t compare it with the figures of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F7BCFE4EFEEBFDD2" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcylindricus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F7BCFE4EFEEBFDD2" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. subcylindricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F3E7FD92FDAAFDD2" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[474,635,511,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="188 - 278" refId="ref11264" refString="Kataev, B. M. (1989) New data on the ground-beetles of the genera Pangus and Harpalus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) with a revision of some Palaeartic species groups Nasekomye Mongolii. Vol. 10. Nauka, Leningrad, 188 - 278. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Kataev (1989)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F09CFE6DFC56FDD2" author="Marggi, W. &amp; Luka, H. &amp; Huber, C. &amp; Wrase, D. W. &amp; Durrer, H." box="[673,903,511,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="195 - 202" refId="ref11838" refString="Marggi, W., Luka, H., Huber, C., Wrase, D. W. &amp; Durrer, H. (2010) Harpalus (s. str.) subcylindricus Dejean, 1829 (Coleoptera, Carabidae) auch in der Schweiz und im Elsass (F). Entomologische Blatter, 106, 195 - 202." type="journal article" year="2010">Marggi et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935F8E02F60DFE6DFB46FDD2" box="[1072,1175,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">lectotype</typeStatus>
matches the characters nowadays considered as diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F069FDB6FCCAFDF6" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[596,795,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcylindricus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F069FDB6FCCAFDF6" box="[596,795,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. subcylindricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A key to separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F1CBFDB6FA99FDF6" authority="(Duftschmid, 1812)" baseAuthorityName="Duftschmid" baseAuthorityYear="1812" box="[1014,1352,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anxius">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F1CBFDB6FBB3FDF6" box="[1014,1122,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. anxius</emphasis>
(Duftschmid, 1812)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935F8E02F7BCFDB6FEEBFDAA" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcylindricus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935F8E02F7BCFDB6FEEBFDAA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">H. subcylindricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935F8E02F3F4FDDAFDB7FDAA" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[457,614,583,610]" pageId="6" pageNumber="490" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. This last species shows a Centro Asiatic European distribution pattern, from western 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935F8E02F30EFDF9FEA7FD4E" box="[307,374,619,645]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="490">China</collectingCountry>
to the Iberian Peninsula.
</paragraph>
